					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>252 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>105</height>
										<width>75</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>65</height>
										<width>43</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>252 folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern paper flyleaf and 1 unfoliated vellum flyleaf at the beginning, and 6 unfoliated veullm flyleaves and 1 modern paper flyleaf at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each, marked with catchwords and signed with Hebrew letters at the end.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="13" writtenLines="13">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible plummet ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Small Italian square and semi-cursive scripts of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 251v, 252r&amp;v contain attempts by someone learning to write Hebrew.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
